    "title": "Real-world average",
    "prompt": "Adam's average homework score, worth 40% of his grade, is 76%. His average unit test score, worth another 40%, was 81%. The final makes up the rest of his total grade. How many questions does he need to answer correctly on the 50-question final to earn a B (80%) in the class?",
    "description": null,
    "hint": "A percent is a fraction, converted to a decimal, and multiplied by 100. You should use a weighted average to find the answer.",
    "directions": null,
    "order": 11,
    "time_limit": null,
    "feedback": "This is called a weighted average. The sum of all the weighted averages of Adam's scores will be 80. Let <i>x<\/i> be his score on the final, which you can see is worth \r\n\r\n<math>\r\n\u00a0<mrow> <mn>100<\/mn><mo>\u2212<\/mo><mn>40<\/mn><mo>\u2212<\/mo><mn>40<\/mn><mo>=<\/mo><mn>20<\/mn><mi>%<\/mi><\/mrow>\r\n<\/math> of his score. Write and solve an equation.<br\/>\r\n\r\n<math> \u00a0<mtable> \u00a0\u00a0<mtr> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mtd> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mn>.4<\/mn><mrow><mo>(<\/mo>\r\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mrow> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mn>76<\/mn><\/mrow> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mo>)<\/mo><\/mrow><mo>+<\/mo><mn>.4<\/mn><mrow><mo>(<\/mo>\r\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mrow> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mn>81<\/mn><\/mrow> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mo>)<\/mo><\/mrow><mo>+<\/mo><mn>.2<\/mn><mi>x<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><mn>80<\/mn>\r\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/mtd> \u00a0\u00a0<\/mtr> \u00a0\u00a0<mtr> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mtd> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mn>30.4<\/mn><mo>+<\/mo><mn>32.4<\/mn><mo>+<\/mo><mn>.2<\/mn><mi>x<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><mn>80<\/mn>\r\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/mtd> \u00a0\u00a0<\/mtr> \u00a0\u00a0<mtr> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mtd> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mn>.2<\/mn><mi>x<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><mn>17.2<\/mn>\r\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/mtd> \u00a0\u00a0<\/mtr> \u00a0\u00a0<mtr> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mtd> \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<mi>x<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><mn>86<\/mn>\r\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/mtd> \u00a0\u00a0<\/mtr> \u00a0<\/mtable> \u00a0\r\n\r\n<\/math> \r\n<br\/> So, he needs an 86%, which is 86 of 100 questions. Since there are only 50 questions, divide by 2. Adam needs to answer 43 questions correctly to get a B.",
